### Version B — call validation Function (Logic App uses the same HTTP shape)
@baseUrl = http://localhost:7071
@apiPath = /api

### Validate — valid payload
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPath}}/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Alex Lee",
  "employee_email": "alex@example.com",
  "amount": 42.50,
  "category": "travel",
  "description": "Taxi",
  "manager_email": "mgr@example.com"
}

### Validate — missing fields (invalid)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPath}}/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Alex Lee",
  "amount": 50
}

### Validate — invalid category
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPath}}/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Alex Lee",
  "employee_email": "alex@example.com",
  "amount": 50,
  "category": "not_a_category",
  "description": "x",
  "manager_email": "mgr@example.com"
}

### Register pending approval (Logic App calls after validation for amount >= 100)
@cid = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPath}}/pending/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "correlationId": "{{cid}}",
  "expense": {
    "employee_name": "Alex Lee",
    "employee_email": "alex@example.com",
    "amount": 150,
    "category": "meals",
    "description": "Dinner",
    "manager_email": "mgr@example.com"
  }
}

### Poll status (Logic App Until loop)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPath}}/pending/{{cid}}/status

### Manager decision (simulates manager approval)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPath}}/pending/{{cid}}/decision
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "decision": "approve"
}
